    {
      "id": "879008595303888",
      "score": 1,
      "review_title": "Not Worth It",
      "review_description": "I played this game with my friend Loganington because the art and pictures displayed on the shop looked intriguing. We played for ~15 minutes, and I already got a scope on what the game has to offer; lag, unoptimized graphics, and stolen assets.\nWhen you load in, there isn’t much tutorialing on where you are. You have to figure out yourself that you’re in tutorial and find the button for the flashlight (which is helpfully a, although it doesn’t do much).\nThe maps are unreasonably dark and combined with the lag, it’s very hard to traverse. The stolen assets are from Gorilla Tag, including the player model, trees, and many other items. The monsters are somewhat… intriguing (and I mean this negatively), and the AI for said monsters are less than good. \nIt’s just not worth your time, and there are plenty of other horror gorilla tag-esque games out there that outshine this one by a mile.",
      "date": 1766633416,
      "review_helpful_count": 9,
      "author_display_name": "sixkVI",
